---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PillarCard from '../components/PillarCard.astro';
import AvatarCard from '../components/AvatarCard.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Crown and Compass | A Brotherhood for Men"
  description="A peer-led Christian men's community built around reading, honest conversation, and The Walk. Free. No ranks. No performance."
>

  <!-- ======================================================
       HERO
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="hero grain-bg">
    <video class="hero-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline aria-hidden="true">
      <source src="/bg1.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
    </video>
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Crown &amp; Compass</p>
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The Walk is long.<br />
        No man takes it alone.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-subtext">
        A small group of Christian men who read a book together<br class="desktop-only" />
        and talk honestly about their lives. Free. No ranks. No performance.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/compass" class="btn-ghost">Read The Compass</a>
        <a href="/join" class="btn-amber">Join a Chapter</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======================================================
       WHAT CC IS
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-container">
      <div class="what-cc-grid">
        <div class="what-cc-label">
          <p class="overline">What This Is</p>
        </div>
        <div class="what-cc-content">
          <p class="lead-text">
            At first encounter, Crown and Compass is a small group of Christian men who read a book
            together and talk honestly about their lives. That's it. No fees, no ranks, no
            performance. A man shows up on a Saturday morning, hears some other men speak plainly
            about what's hard and what they're grateful for, and realizes other men carry the same
            weight. That is the first thing CC gives him.
          </p>
          <p>
            What it becomes over time is harder to name and more important. It becomes the community
            that makes the Walk possible. A man doesn't grow in isolation. He grows when other men
            are watching, asking, and walking alongside. Crown and Compass is the structure that
            holds that.
          </p>
          <p>
            If a man shows up and stays, here is what CC offers: he will be known by name by men
            who are glad he's there. He will have a place to say the true thing without managing
            how it lands. He will see other men in the middle of the same struggle, which will do
            more for him than any podcast or self-help book. This is not a guarantee of outcomes.
            It is a guarantee of accompaniment. We go together. That's the promise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ======================================================
       WHO IT'S FOR
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p class="overline">Who It's For</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Three kinds of men find their way here.</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid-3">
        <AvatarCard
          headline="The man who built something but feels it's not enough."
          description="He has a job, maybe a family, maybe a faith he grew up with but hasn't touched in years. He's competent. He's responsible. And there's a low-grade sense that something is missing. Most of his friendships are transactional."
        />
        <AvatarCard
          headline="The man who is in over his head."
          description="His marriage is strained, or his business is struggling, or his health is a mess he keeps meaning to address. He's tired of performing okay. He wants someone to ask the real question and actually want the real answer."
        />
        <AvatarCard
          headline="The man who is doing well and knows he can't sustain it alone."
          description="He's read the books, he goes to church, he's done some therapy. He knows the territory. What he needs is men doing the same work. Men who will go with him. Iron sharpens iron. He's looking for the iron."
        />
      </div>
      <p class="cards-footer-text">
        What these three men have in common: they want to be known, they want to grow, and they
        don't know where to find that among men.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ======================================================
       HOW IT WORKS
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="section-pad how-it-works-section">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p class="overline">How It Works</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Four things, all connected.</h2>
      <div class="how-grid">
        <div class="how-item">
          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Chapters icon: group -->
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="3"/>
              <circle cx="17" cy="7" r="3"/>
              <path d="M1 21c0-4 3.6-7 8-7"/>
              <path d="M23 21c0-4-3.6-7-8-7"/>
              <path d="M7 21c0-3 2.2-5.5 5-5.5s5 2.5 5 5.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="how-title">Chapters</h3>
          <p class="how-desc">
            4–8 Brothers who read the current book together and meet to discuss it.
            Weekly, biweekly, or as the group can sustain. The core unit of Crown and Compass.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="how-item">
          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- Guides icon: compass -->
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <polygon points="16.24 7.76 14.12 14.12 7.76 16.24 9.88 9.88 16.24 7.76"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="how-title">Guides</h3>
          <p class="how-desc">
            The Guide is not the teacher or the expert. He's the man who prepared, who holds
            the room, who keeps the conversation honest. Any Brother can Guide. The role rotates.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="how-item">
          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- The Round icon: circle with three dots -->
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="8" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="12" x2="12" y2="12" stroke-width="2"/>
              <line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="16" stroke-width="2"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="how-title">The Round</h3>
          <p class="how-desc">
            Closes every meeting. Three moves: the check-in (<em>where are you, really?</em>),
            The Ask, and The Close. The Round is where the real work happens.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="how-item">
          <div class="how-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <!-- The Compass icon: four directions -->
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/>
              <path d="M12 2v4M12 18v4M2 12h4M18 12h4"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="how-title">The Compass</h3>
          <p class="how-desc">
            CC's long-arc curriculum: four pillars — Body, Being, Balance, Business.
            A map, not a syllabus. The direction for the Walk.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ======================================================
       THE COMPASS STRIP
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="section-pad compass-strip-section">
    <div class="section-container">
      <div class="compass-strip-header">
        <p class="overline">The Compass</p>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Four pillars. One long walk.</h2>
        <p class="compass-strip-sub">
          The Compass is not a self-help program. It is a map. A man picks it up knowing roughly
          where he stands and uses it to walk.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar-grid">
        <PillarCard
          name="Body"
          hook="Tend what you have been given. Not for aesthetics — for presence."
          href="/compass#body"
        />
        <PillarCard
          name="Being"
          hook="The inner life shapes everything downstream. Guard your heart."
          href="/compass#being"
        />
        <PillarCard
          name="Balance"
          hook="Who gets the actual you? The real one. The one who is present."
          href="/compass#balance"
        />
        <PillarCard
          name="Business"
          hook="Does your work serve your life, or have you become fuel for it?"
          href="/compass#business"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="compass-strip-cta">
        <a href="/compass" class="btn-ghost">Read The Full Compass</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <!-- ======================================================
       A WORD FROM BRIAN
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="section-container">
      <div class="brian-quote-wrapper">
        <blockquote class="brian-quote">
          <p>
            I started Crown and Compass because I needed it. Not because I had answers — because
            I was tired of carrying things alone.
          </p>
          <p>
            There's something that happens when a man says the true thing in a room of men who
            are glad he's there. I've seen it. It changes a man slowly, over time. Not all at
            once. The Walk is long. But something moves.
          </p>
          <p>
            What we're building is simple: a place where men can be honest with each other and
            with God, around a book, every week, for as long as it takes. That's it. That's enough.
          </p>
          <cite>— Brian, Founder</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======================================================
       JOIN CTA
  ====================================================== -->
  <section class="join-cta grain-bg">
    <div class="section-container join-cta-inner">
      <h2 class="join-cta-heading">
        Crown and Compass is free.<br />It has always been free.
      </h2>
      <p class="join-cta-sub">
        Free because the Gospel is free. Free because the best communities have never charged
        for belonging. If you want to walk, reach out.
      </p>
      <a href="/join" class="btn-amber">Get Connected</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ---- Hero ---- */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 92vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    background-color: var(--bg-base);
    padding: 6rem 1.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-video {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    opacity: 0.18;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    max-width: 52rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .hero-subtext {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.125rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  .hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .desktop-only {
    display: none;
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .desktop-only { display: inline; }
  }

  /* ---- Overline / section label ---- */
  .overline {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  /* ---- What CC Is ---- */
  .what-cc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .what-cc-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  .what-cc-label .overline {
    margin-top: 0.375rem;
  }

  .what-cc-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .lead-text {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 2.5vw, 1.3125rem);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .what-cc-content p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ---- Who It's For ---- */
  .cards-grid-3 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .cards-grid-3 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .cards-footer-text {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  /* ---- How It Works ---- */
  .how-it-works-section {
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .how-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .how-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 3rem 4rem;
    }
  }

  .how-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .how-icon {
    color: var(--accent);
    opacity: 0.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .how-title {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .how-desc {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Compass Strip ---- */
  .compass-strip-header {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .compass-strip-sub {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: -1.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .pillar-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background-color: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 480px) {
    .pillar-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .pillar-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .compass-strip-cta {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  /* ---- Brian's Quote ---- */
  .brian-quote-wrapper {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .brian-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 0.25rem 0 0.25rem 2rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .brian-quote p {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .brian-quote p:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .brian-quote cite {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* ---- Join CTA ---- */
  .join-cta {
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .join-cta-inner {
    text-align: center;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .join-cta-heading {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .join-cta-sub {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 36rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
